) on M368?”, the latter presumably an error for M.468. A skull labelled M.469 (
Fig. 4
), fourth molars not fully erupted, is thus doubtfully associated with skin M.469. The MAMU Register entry for M.469, done in the 1960s, states, “skin only, skull attached to M.468?”. Since that entry, a second skull has apparently been found in the Collection and doubtfully matched with skin M.469 but the basis of this match, when it was done, and by whom is not recorded in the database.
